From: Armbian
Subject: orangepi-win: USB1 VBUS (PD7) + USB host

Rebased onto v2026.07-rc4's orangepi_win_defconfig. Carries the USB host VBUS
(PD7) + USB_HOST bits from the old fix-usb1-vbus-opiwin patch. Dropped the patch's
SPL_SPI_FLASH_SUPPORT: it broke boot on this A64 (SPL-stage); pure-upstream A64
u-boot boots fine (confirmed on lime-a64), so SPL_SPI was the culprit. SPI-flash
boot can be revisited separately if needed. The DT reg_usb1_vbus half is also
dropped (kernel powers USB via its dtb; u-boot driving PD7 carries the state in).

--- a/configs/orangepi_win_defconfig
+++ b/configs/orangepi_win_defconfig
@@ -12,3 +12,5 @@
 CONFIG_SPI=y
 CONFIG_USB_EHCI_HCD=y
 CONFIG_USB_OHCI_HCD=y
+CONFIG_USB1_VBUS_PIN="PD7"
+CONFIG_USB_HOST=y
